<section id="howto" class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-20">
  <p class="text-xs font-mono text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-widest mb-4">Getting Started</p>
  <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-12">How to use SHABBAT.md</h2>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12">
    <div class="space-y-10">
      <div class="flex gap-5">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-blue-600 text-white flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-bold">1</div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Add SHABBAT.md to your repo</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 leading-relaxed">Create a <code class="bg-gray-100 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded font-mono text-xs">SHABBAT.md</code> at the root of your repository. Most Shabbat-aware agents will find it automatically.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-5">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-blue-600 text-white flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-bold">2</div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Declare the agent's identity</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 leading-relaxed">Set <code class="bg-gray-100 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded font-mono text-xs">identity_type</code>. This is the single most consequential field — it determines whether amirah l'akum concerns apply.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-5">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-blue-600 text-white flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-bold">3</div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Define the Shabbat window</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 leading-relaxed">Set your timezone and let the agent compute accurate <em>zmanim</em> (halachic times). Or specify exact ISO 8601 times for strict control.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-5">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-blue-600 text-white flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-bold">4</div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Scope permitted and forbidden actions</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 leading-relaxed">List what the agent may and may not do. Map each capability to the melachot table. When in doubt, leave it out of the permitted list.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="flex gap-5">
        <div class="flex-shrink-0 w-8 h-8 rounded-full bg-blue-600 text-white flex items-center justify-center text-sm font-bold">5</div>
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Enable the Havdalah Audit</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 leading-relaxed">After Shabbat ends, the agent surfaces a log of all actions taken during the window. Review it — analogous to reviewing what your Shabbos goy did while you were away.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div>
      <p class="text-xs font-mono text-gray-400 mb-3">Shabbos Clock pattern</p>
      <div class="code-block mb-6">
        <div class="code-label"><span>zmanim integration (Python)</span></div>
        <pre><span class="comment"># pip install zmanim</span>
<span class="key">from</span> zmanim <span class="key">import</span> Zmanim

zmanim = Zmanim(
    geo=user_location,
    date=friday
)

agent.pause_at  = zmanim.shkia()
agent.resume_at = zmanim.tzait_hakochavim(saturday)</pre>
      </div>

      <p class="text-xs font-mono text-gray-400 mb-3">Scope lock before Shabbat</p>
      <div class="code-block">
        <div class="code-label"><span>scope-lock.json</span></div>
        <pre>{
  <span class="key">"shabbat_mode"</span>: <span class="value-bool">true</span>,
  <span class="key">"allowed_tools"</span>: [
    <span class="value-string">"read"</span>,
    <span class="value-string">"search"</span>,
    <span class="value-string">"summarize"</span>
  ],
  <span class="key">"forbidden_tools"</span>: [
    <span class="value-string">"write"</span>, <span class="value-string">"deploy"</span>,
    <span class="value-string">"delete"</span>, <span class="value-string">"send_email"</span>,
    <span class="value-string">"charge"</span>, <span class="value-string">"commit"</span>
  ],
  <span class="key">"hitl_disabled"</span>: <span class="value-bool">true</span>,
  <span class="key">"resume_at"</span>: <span class="value-string">"&lt;havdalah_iso8601&gt;"</span>
}</pre>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- FAQ -->
<section id="faq" class="bg-gray-50 border-t border-gray-100 py-20">
  <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6">
    <p class="text-xs font-mono text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-widest mb-4">She'elot u'Teshuvot</p>
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-12">FAQ</h2>

    <div class="max-w-2xl space-y-8">
      <% [
        {
          q: "Is SHABBAT.md a halachic authority?",
          a: "No. SHABBAT.md is a configuration format and a framework for asking the right questions. It can identify the question; it cannot replace a qualified posek (halachic decisor). Novel edge cases — and AI agents are genuinely new territory — require a rabbi familiar with technology. This file will tell you to consult one when you're in SAFEK territory."
        },
        {
          q: "What if my agent needs to run during Shabbat for a genuine emergency?",
          a: "Set life_safety_override: true in SHABBAT.md. Pikuach nefesh (saving a life) overrides all of Shabbat, by unanimous halachic consensus. This field is intentionally not gated — emergencies don't wait for configuration reviews."
        },
        {
          q: "Does this apply to Yom Tov (Jewish holidays) too?",
          a: "Set observe_yom_tov: true and SHABBAT.md will apply the same framework to Yom Tov. Note that some melachot are permitted on Yom Tov when directly serving human needs (ochel nefesh), but their compute equivalents are narrow. The framework errs conservative unless you explicitly expand the permitted list for Yom Tov."
        },
        {
          q: "What's the difference between shkia and candle-lighting as pause_trigger?",
          a: "Shkia is halachic sunset — the start of Shabbat. Candle-lighting is typically 18 minutes earlier, a custom fence around the Shabbat boundary. Conservative users may prefer candle-lighting as the trigger. Both are computed from accurate zmanim for the agent's configured timezone."
        },
        {
          q: "What about an agent that runs in a datacenter I own? Shvitat keilim?",
          a: "Shvitat keilim (your tools resting) is a rabbinic concern distinct from melachah. An agent running on infrastructure you own but don't personally operate, under its own identity, is in SAFEK territory. Most contemporary poskim are lenient on passive automation in owned systems started before Shabbat — but consult a rabbi."
        },
        {
          q: "Can I have multiple SHABBAT.md files in a monorepo?",
          a: "Yes. Place a SHABBAT.md in each subdirectory. The nearest file takes precedence. This mirrors how AGENTS.md works — per-subproject configuration is encouraged when different agents have different capabilities and compliance requirements."
        },
        {
          q: "Are there required fields?",
          a: "Only identity_type and timezone are required. Everything else has safe defaults (conservative). SHABBAT.md is standard Markdown — the format is intentionally human-readable and agent-parseable without a strict schema."
        },
      ].each do |item| %>
      <div>
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2 text-base"><%= item[:q] %></h3>
        <p class="text-gray-500 text-sm leading-relaxed"><%= item[:a] %></p>
      </div>
      <% end %>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

